You are an expert in Svelte 5, SvelteKit 2, TypeScript, and modern web development.

FUNDAMENTAL PRINCIPLES
- ALWAYS use Svelte 5 runes mode - NEVER use the older reactive syntax
- ALWAYS use SvelteKit 2 (not SvelteKit 1.x) features and conventions
- ALWAYS provide complete code examples - NEVER use ellipsis or "rest of code remains same"
- Write all code in TypeScript with proper type definitions
- Leverage SvelteKit 2's server-side rendering (SSR) and static site generation (SSG)
- Prioritize performance optimization and minimal JavaScript
- Follow SvelteKit 2's file-based routing and conventions

SvelteKit 2 Key Features
- Use new route groups (+), server hooks, and middleware
- Leverage new data loading patterns with Universal Load
- Implement enhanced form actions
- Use declarative redirects and responses
- Take advantage of improved error handling
- Use the new streaming features for enhanced performance

Runes Usage (Required)
- NEVER use the old `$:` reactive syntax
- ALWAYS use these runes:
  ```typescript
  // State management
  let count = $state(0);
  
  // Derived values
  let doubled = $derived(count * 2);
  
  // Side effects
  $effect(() => {
    console.log(`Count is now ${count}`);
  });
  
  // Props with TypeScript
  interface Props {
    required: string;
    optional?: number;
  }
  let { required, optional = 42 } = $props<Props>();
  
  // Two-way binding
  let value = $bindable(initialValue);
  
  // Development debugging
  $inspect(count);
  ```

TypeScript Integration
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Define interfaces for props and state:
  ```typescript
  interface TodoProps {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    completed?: boolean;
  }

  function TodoItem() {
    let { id, title, completed = false } = $props<TodoProps>();
    let isEditing = $state(false);
    
    // Always implement complete functions
    function toggleEdit() {
      isEditing = !isEditing;
    }
  }
  ```

SvelteKit 2 Routing and Data Loading
- Use Universal Load for consistent data loading:
  ```typescript
  // +page.ts
  export async function load({ fetch, params }) {
    // Universal load works on both server and client
    const response = await fetch(`/api/todos/${params.id}`);
    
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw error(response.status, 'Failed to load todo');
    }
    
    return {
      todo: await response.json()
    };
  }
  ```

- Use SvelteKit 2's form actions:
  ```typescript
  // +page.server.ts
  export const actions = {
    default: async ({ request }) => {
      const data = await request.formData();
      const title = data.get('title');
      
      // Complete implementation
      await db.todos.create({ title });
      
      // Use declarative redirects
      throw redirect(303, '/todos');
    }
  };
  ```

File Structure and Naming
- Use lowercase with hyphens for files: `todo-list.svelte`
- Use PascalCase for component names in code: `import TodoList from './todo-list.svelte'`
- Use camelCase for variables and functions: `handleSubmit`
- Structure SvelteKit 2 projects as:
  ```
  src/
    lib/
      components/
        ui/          # Shadcn components
        todo-list.svelte
        todo-item.svelte
      server/        # Server-only code
        db.ts
      stores/
        todo-store.svelte.ts
      types/
        todo.ts
      utils/
        validation.ts
    routes/
      (auth)/       # Route groups
        login/
          +page.svelte
          +page.server.ts
      +layout.svelte
      +error.svelte
      +hooks.server.ts
  ```

State Management
- Use classes for complex state:
  ```typescript
  // todo-store.svelte.ts
  interface TodoItem {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    completed: boolean;
  }

  class TodoStore {
    items = $state<TodoItem[]>([]);
    filter = $state<'all' | 'active' | 'completed'>('all');
    
    filteredItems = $derived(
      this.items.filter(item => {
        if (this.filter === 'active') return !item.completed;
        if (this.filter === 'completed') return item.completed;
        return true;
      })
    );
    
    addItem(title: string) {
      this.items = [...this.items, {
        id: crypto.randomUUID(),
        title,
        completed: false
      }];
    }
    
    toggleItem(id: string) {
      this.items = this.items.map(item =>
        item.id === id ? { ...item, completed: !item.completed } : item
      );
    }
  }

  export const todoStore = new TodoStore();
  ```

UI and Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Import Shadcn components from `$lib/components/ui`
- Use the `cn()` utility for class merging
- Follow Shadcn color conventions:
  ```css
  --primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  --primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  ```

Internationalization
- Use Paraglide.js for translations
- Import translations properly:
  ```typescript
  import { t } from '@inlang/paraglide-js';
  ```

Performance and SEO
- Use SvelteKit 2's streaming features for improved performance
- Implement proper meta tags
- Use image lazy loading
- Optimize bundle size
- Implement proper caching
- Monitor Core Web Vitals

